==English==

===Adjective===

'''plausible'''

#Seemingly or apparently valid, likely, or [[acceptable]]; [[credible]]: a plausible excuse.
#Worthy of being [[applaud]]ed; [[praiseworthy]]; [[commendable]]; [[ready]].
#Obtaining [[approbation]]; specifically [[pleasing]]; apparently [[right]]; [[specious]]; as, ''a plausible pretext''; ''plausible manners''; ''a plausible delusion''.
#Using specious [[argument]]s or [[discourse]]; as, ''a plausible speaker''.

